o longer cause players to fall through geometry.&lt;br&gt;-- Getting out of water should be much easier to do. &lt;br&gt;-- Berzerker: Hastenend War Cry should be fixed now.&lt;br&gt;-- If your stored AA's go above 30, they will no longer be set to 30 when you zone. However, you should still not be able to gain more than 30 unless you get a refund, get the AA from a GM, or get an AA from a script.&lt;br&gt;-- Spell scribe timers (putting a new spell into the spell book) now take only 1 second.&lt;br&gt;-- Players should no longer experience 20k falls when standing on cliff edges while suffering from low framerate. Please be on the lookout for collision problems and /bug with detailed locations if you experience any.&lt;br&gt;-- Fixed an issue with Half Elf Paladins of Tunare and the Origin AA.&lt;br&gt;-- The bounding radius for small races was too tall, preventing them from accessing some areas. For example, gnomes couldn't enter the small huts in steamfont. This was a global problem, that is just an example. Please be on the lookout for any movement or collision issues related to small races.&lt;br&gt;-- You may notice various NPCs that had been standing on tents or otherwise not where they should be are now properly positioned. Please bug any NPCs you see that appear to be incorrectly placed.&lt;br&gt;-- Weather effects should now be working properly when the Wake of Karana spell is used.&lt;br&gt;-- Sounds related to starting &amp; stopping of various weather types due to zoning and Wake of Karana should be working correctly.&lt;br&gt;-- Added NO_PET to item description window which will be displayed when an item has this flag.&lt;br&gt;-- Changed /who commands to display both class title and base class name for players over level 50, e.g. "Bedazzler (Enchanter)"&lt;br&gt;-- Fixed a bug that caused a lot of writing to the dbg.txt file during a raid&lt;br&gt;-- Bazaar trader mode is no longer cancelled when going from windowed to full-screen and vice-versa.&lt;br